    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - REAR PTO HOUSING ASSEMBLY REMOVAL (IF EQUIPPED) - INSTALLING REAR PTO HOUSING
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="11">
        <title>INSTALLING REAR PTO HOUSING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lay the Rear PTO housing assembly with the transmission side face down.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>BE SURE O-RING GROOVES (1 LARGE AND 3 SMALL) ARE CLEAN AND FREE OF ALL OLD SEALANT MATERIAL.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install one (1) large O-Ring (
                <emph type="bold">1, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600742">7.42</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) and three (3) small O-Rings (
                <emph type="bold">2, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600742">7.42</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) into the O-Ring grooves using Aviation Permatex #3.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two (2) hollow dowel pins into Rear PTO housing assembly (
                <emph type="bold">3, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600742">7.42</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="underscr">BE SURE</emph>
                        STUD IS INSTALLED INTO CRANKCASE BEFORE INSTALLING REAR PTO HOUSING ASSEMBLY.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect threads and replace stud if necessary. Install stud into crankcase. (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600743">7.43</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1600742" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5291" filename="../figeg5/eg5291.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.42 O-Ring And Dowel Pin Locations</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">1. Large O-Ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">2. Small O-Ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">3. Hollow Dowel Pin Locations</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600743" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg7224" filename="../figeg7/eg7224.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.43 PTO Mounting Stud Location</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new camshaft O-Ring over camshaft end opening at rear of crankcase (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600744">7.44</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="underscr">BE SURE</emph>
                        A NEW CAMSHAFT O-RING IS INSTALLED BEFORE PROCEEDING ANY FURTHER WITH THIS PROCEDURE.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two (2) guide dowel pins, used during removal procedure, into crankshaft flange at
                the 3 and 9 o'clock positions (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600745">7.45</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If not already done remove the four (4) pipe plugs from the Rear PTO housing assembly.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1600744" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg7225" filename="../figeg7/eg7225.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.44 Installing Camshaft O-Ring</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">1. Camshaft O-Ring</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600745" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5279" filename="../figeg5/eg5279.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.45 Installing Guide Dowel Pins</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Be sure installation tool ZTSE4415 is installed into the pto housing crankshaft opening (2,
                        figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600746">7.46</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the Rear PTO housing assembly and align with the crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slowly guide the Rear PTO housing assembly over the two (2) guide pins mounted in the
                crankshaft (
                <emph type="bold">1, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600746">7.46</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) and studs mounted in the crankcase. Install the seven (7) mounting bolts and tighten to the special
                torque value (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600746">7.46</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install special nut (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600747">7.47</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) over the crankcase stud.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Hand tighten special nut at the upper hollow dowel location (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600748">7.48</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1600746" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg7226" filename="../figeg7/eg7226.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.46 PTO Housing Installed On To Crankcase</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">1. Guide Pins</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">2. Installation Tool</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600747" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg7228" filename="../figeg7/eg7228.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.47 Special Mounting Nut</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600748" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg7227" filename="../figeg7/eg7227.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.48 Tighten Special Mounting Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the special nut to the special torque value (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600749">7.49</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="underscr">DO NOT REMOVE</emph>
                        rear oil seal installation tool or guide pins yet.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the four (4) pipe plugs and tighten (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600750">7.50</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove lifting eye from Rear PTO housing assembly.</para>
            <figure id="ef1600749" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg7229" filename="../figeg7/eg7229.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.49 Tighten Special Mounting Nut To The Special Torque Value</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600750" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg7230" filename="../figeg7/eg7230.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.50 Installing Pipe Plugs</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install lubrication supply elbow and connect the lubrication supply tube to the crankcase
                and Rear PTO housing assembly. Tighten the nuts securing the tube to the fittings (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600751">7.51</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the steel rod of the installation tool (
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE4415</emph>) through the hole (
                <emph type="bold">2, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600752">7.52</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) of the tube assembly (
                <emph type="bold">1, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600752">7.52</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="underscr">Do not</emph>
                        pull the tube assembly out.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull out on the steel rod until the tube assembly (
                <emph type="bold">1, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600752">7.52</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) comes out together with the cover assembly (
                <emph type="bold">3, Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600752">7.52</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) of installation tool
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE4415</emph>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Push the input gear towards the engine until the input gear reaches the mating surface of
                the crankshaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply grease to the inner surface of the wear sleeve/rear oil seal before pressing it onto
                the input gear.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1600751" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5289" filename="../figeg5/eg5289.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.51 PTO Lubrication Tube</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">1. Elbow</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">2. Nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">3. Lubrication Tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600752" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg7231" filename="../figeg7/eg7231.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.52 Rear Oil Seal Installation Tool</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">1. Tube Assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">2. Steel Rod Location</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">3. Cover Assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">20. Press the seal into the cover using the oil seal driver and a hammer (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e160_183.xml" xrefid="ef1600753">7.53</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
